in Shimeji-ee! Here's some recommended places to start looking.<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;br />gt;\n<lt;div class=\"gamesimagebox\">gt;<lt;img src=\"images/cachomon.png\" alt=\"Cachomon.com\" />gt;<lt;/div>gt;<lt;div class=\"centre\">gt;\n<lt;h2>gt;Cachomon.com<lt;/h2>gt;\nContains hundreds of Shimeji characters from popular culture all made by the Cachomon team! You'll find Shimeji here that make the most of the special features made available by my version of Shimeji-ee. \nCommissions are also available for those looking to bring their own characters to life. Check out what's on offer today!\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"https://cachomon.com/grid.php?g=1\" target=\"_blank\">gt;Visit Site<lt;/a>gt;\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;br class=\"separator\" />gt;<lt;hr />gt;\n<lt;div class=\"gamesimagebox\">gt;<lt;img src=\"images/dagroup.png\" alt=\"\" />gt;<lt;/div>gt;<lt;div class=\"centre\">gt;\n<lt;h2>gt;Shimeji Desktop Pets deviantArt Group<lt;/h2>gt;\nWhile deviantArt has declining relevance since its takeover by Wix and subsequent mismanagement, including the deluge of AI slop that has plagued the platform, the Shimeji Desktop Pets group still contains some hidden gems that should make it worth your time to check out. New releases of Shimeji-ee, as well as new shimeji characters, are still regularly posted there.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"http://shimejidesktoppets.deviantart.com/\" target=\"_blank\">gt;Visit Site<lt;/a>gt;\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;br class=\"separator\" />gt;<lt;hr />gt;\n<lt;div class=\"gamesimagebox\">gt;<lt;img src=\"images/search.png\" alt=\"\" />gt;<lt;/div>gt;<lt;div class=\"centre\">gt;\n<lt;h2>gt;Search Online for Shimeji<lt;/h2>gt;\nSeveral major art websites can be useful destinations for discovering new Shimeji-ee characters. It's worth checking shimeji tags on any art gallery or social media site you find. Keep in mind that shimeji <lt;em>gt;are<lt;/em>gt; a type of Japanese mushroom so you might have a few mushroomy results crop up as you search.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;For convenience I've included two searches you can try.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"https://www.deviantart.com/tag/shimeji\" target=\"_blank\">gt;deviantArt<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"https://www.pixiv.net/en/tags/%E3%81%97%E3%82%81%E3%81%98/artworks\" target=\"_blank\">gt;pixiv<lt;/a>gt;\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;br class=\"separator\" />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\n<lt;script async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-6755552884610204\"\n     crossorigin=\"anonymous\">gt;<lt;/script>gt;\n<lt;!-- Kilkakon.com Footer -->gt;\n<lt;ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\n     style=\"display:block\"\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6755552884610204\"\n     data-ad-slot=\"0063859132\"\n     data-ad-format=\"auto\"\n     data-full-width-responsive=\"true\">gt;<lt;/ins>gt;\n<lt;script>gt;\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n<lt;/script>gt;\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;a name=\"menu\">gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;div class=\"footer\">gt;\n<lt;div class=\"footercontent\">gt;\n<lt;a href=\"../games.php\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerleft\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;Games<lt;/h1>gt;\nGames and epic mods\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;a href=\"../software.php\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerleft\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;Software<lt;/h1>gt;\nTools and fun gadgets\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;a href=\"../downloads.php\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerleft\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;Downloads<lt;/h1>gt;\nMaps, mods and skins\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;!--<lt;a href=\"../bio.php\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerleft\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;Bio<lt;/h1>gt;\nAbout me\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;-->gt;<lt;a href=\"http://youtube.com/konfluxgames\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerright\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;YouTube<lt;/h1>gt;\nGaming channel\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/Kilkakon\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerright\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;Patreon<lt;/h1>gt;\nSupport me\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;a href=\"../contact.php\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerright\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;Email<lt;/h1>gt;\nContact me\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;a href=\"https://discord.gg/kHwgcka\">gt;<lt;div class=\"footerright\">gt;\n<lt;h1>gt;Discord<lt;/h1>gt;\nJoin the community\n<lt;/div>gt;<lt;/a>gt;\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;/body>gt;\n<lt;/html>gt;","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_PhoFa1ihXasqkz2uWPhnBB9s","type":"tool_result","content":"<lt;html>gt;<lt;head>gt;<lt;title>gt;Kilkakon.com - Shimeji-ee Affordances Tutorial<lt;/title>gt;\n<lt;link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"../konflux.ico\" />gt;\n<lt;link href=\"../style.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />gt;\n<lt;meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">gt;<lt;/head>gt;<lt;body>gt;\n<lt;div class=\"header\">gt;<lt;img src=\"../images/mobilebanner.png\" alt=\"Kilkakon.com\">gt;<lt;a href=\"#menu\" class=\"transparent\">gt;<lt;img src=\"../images/mobilemenu.png\" alt=\"Menu\" class=\"right\" />gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;div class=\"main\">gt;<lt;div class=\"centre\">gt;<lt;h1>gt;Shimeji-ee Affordances Tutorial<lt;/h1>gt;\n<lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"shimejiee.zip\">gt;Download Now<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"characters.php\">gt;New Characters<lt;/a>gt;\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S7fPCGh5xxo\">gt;Video<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A1y9C1Vbn6Q\">gt;FAQ Video<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"affordances.php\">gt;Affordances Tutorial<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"shimejieesrc.zip\">gt;Source Code<lt;/a>gt; \n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nThis tutorial will walk you through the various steps required to make an interaction animation between two different shimeji. It expects you to have a working understanding of how to edit the xml files to add frames and the like.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nYou can also download <lt;a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/shimeji-example-30523369\">gt;a working example<lt;/a>gt; for free from <lt;a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/shimeji-example-30523369\">gt;my Patreon<lt;/a>gt;. Note that this version is not guaranteed to be using the latest version of Shimeji-ee, so if you plan to use this particular example for your own shimeji you should update it to the latest version.\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;hr />gt;\nInteractive actions have the following components:\n<lt;ol>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;A shimeji <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;s an affordance<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;Other shimeji detect this affordance and move towards it (<lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt;)<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;Once the shimeji meet, they <lt;code>gt;Interact<lt;/code>gt;. If the interaction finishes successfully, they change to the given new <lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt;. Otherwise, they continue as normal in their respective sequences.\n<lt;/ol>gt;\n<lt;h2>gt;Broadcast<lt;/h2>gt;\nLet's start with broadcast. There are three versions:\n<lt;ul>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;BroadcastStay<lt;/code>gt;<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;BroadcastMove<lt;/code>gt;<lt;/li>gt;\n<lt;/ul>gt;\nThese correspond to <lt;code>gt;Animate<lt;/code>gt;, <lt;code>gt;Stay<lt;/code>gt; and <lt;code>gt;Move<lt;/code>gt; respectively, and work in the same way.<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nFor this example, let's make a <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt; action. Take the sit action of the shimeji you want and make a copy of it.<lt;br />gt;\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"Sit\" Type=\"Stay\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime11.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"0,0\" Duration=\"250\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nThen, modify it so it becomes a <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt; action instead of a <lt;code>gt;Stay<lt;/code>gt; as shown in the code snippet below.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nNote the new parameter, <lt;code>gt;Affordance<lt;/code>gt;. Any shimeji searching for an affordance will need to use this same value.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"SitAffordance\" Type=\"Embedded\" Class=\"com.group_finity.mascot.action.Broadcast\" Affordance=\"Cuddle\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime11.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"0,0\" Duration=\"250\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nCreate a new sequence for the action as normal.<lt;br />gt;\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"BroadcastAffordance\" Type=\"Sequence\"&gt;\n    &lt;ActionReference Name=\"SitAffordance\" /&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nAdd the new action into <lt;code>gt;behaviors.xml<lt;/code>gt; as appropriate. I recommend a high frequency as it relies on another shimeji noticing it.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nFor this example, place it in the \"On the Floor\" condition block.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Behavior Name=\"BroadcastAffordance\" Frequency=\"1200\" /&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\n<lt;h2>gt;ScanMove<lt;/h2>gt;\n<lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt; refers to moving towards a target shimeji that is <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;ing the affordance of interest.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nStart by making a copy of the run action in the shimeji that will be looking to <lt;code>gt;Interact<lt;/code>gt; with the first shimeji, as seen here.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"Run\" Type=\"Move\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime2.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime3.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nModify the action to the new <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt; type. Take note of the new attributes:\n<lt;ul>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;Affordance<lt;/code>gt;: The same name as you used before, in the <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt; action. These values must match!<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt;: When the shimeji reaches the <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;ing shimeji, this is the <lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt; (not <lt;code>gt;Action<lt;/code>gt;) to change to.<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;TargetBehavior<lt;/code>gt;: The same, but for the <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;ing shimeji, not the <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt;-ing one.<lt;/li>gt;\n<lt;/ul>gt;\nNote that the behaviour properties are expecting <lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt; names, which typically refer to sequences, not <lt;code>gt;Action<lt;/code>gt;s with image frames.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"RunAffordance\" Type=\"Embedded\" Class=\"com.group_finity.mascot.action.ScanMove\" Affordance=\"Cuddle\" Behavior=\"IHugYou\" TargetBehavior=\"IAmHugged\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime2.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime3.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nCreate a new sequence for the action.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nNote the small Stand before the <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt;&mdash;this is important! Without it the <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt; will not work.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"Hunt\" Type=\"Sequence\"&gt;\n    &lt;ActionReference Name=\"Stand\" Duration=\"${20+Math.random()*20}\" /&gt; &lt;!-- a small delay is needed to prevent an infinite loop --&gt;\n    &lt;ActionReference Name=\"RunAffordance\" /&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nAdd into <lt;code>gt;behaviors.xml<lt;/code>gt; as normal. It should be a high frequency.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"694dc036-8f24-489f-8d74-a9adb4807d3e","uuid":"445b9c9b-1f6b-41ad-9a24-001b8c865476","timestamp":"2026-05-20T09:46:35.020Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"<lt;html>gt;<lt;head>gt;<lt;title>gt;Kilkakon.com - Shimeji-ee Affordances Tutorial<lt;/title>gt;\n<lt;link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"../konflux.ico\" />gt;\n<lt;link href=\"../style.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />gt;\n<lt;meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">gt;<lt;/head>gt;<lt;body>gt;\n<lt;div class=\"header\">gt;<lt;img src=\"../images/mobilebanner.png\" alt=\"Kilkakon.com\">gt;<lt;a href=\"#menu\" class=\"transparent\">gt;<lt;img src=\"../images/mobilemenu.png\" alt=\"Menu\" class=\"right\" />gt;<lt;/a>gt;<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;div class=\"main\">gt;<lt;div class=\"centre\">gt;<lt;h1>gt;Shimeji-ee Affordances Tutorial<lt;/h1>gt;\n<lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"shimejiee.zip\">gt;Download Now<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"characters.php\">gt;New Characters<lt;/a>gt;\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;<lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S7fPCGh5xxo\">gt;Video<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A1y9C1Vbn6Q\">gt;FAQ Video<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"affordances.php\">gt;Affordances Tutorial<lt;/a>gt; <lt;img src=\"../images/logobullet.png\" class=\"middle\" />gt; <lt;a class=\"linkbox\" href=\"shimejieesrc.zip\">gt;Source Code<lt;/a>gt; \n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nThis tutorial will walk you through the various steps required to make an interaction animation between two different shimeji. It expects you to have a working understanding of how to edit the xml files to add frames and the like.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nYou can also download <lt;a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/shimeji-example-30523369\">gt;a working example<lt;/a>gt; for free from <lt;a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/shimeji-example-30523369\">gt;my Patreon<lt;/a>gt;. Note that this version is not guaranteed to be using the latest version of Shimeji-ee, so if you plan to use this particular example for your own shimeji you should update it to the latest version.\n<lt;/div>gt;\n<lt;hr />gt;\nInteractive actions have the following components:\n<lt;ol>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;A shimeji <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;s an affordance<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;Other shimeji detect this affordance and move towards it (<lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt;)<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;Once the shimeji meet, they <lt;code>gt;Interact<lt;/code>gt;. If the interaction finishes successfully, they change to the given new <lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt;. Otherwise, they continue as normal in their respective sequences.\n<lt;/ol>gt;\n<lt;h2>gt;Broadcast<lt;/h2>gt;\nLet's start with broadcast. There are three versions:\n<lt;ul>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;BroadcastStay<lt;/code>gt;<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;BroadcastMove<lt;/code>gt;<lt;/li>gt;\n<lt;/ul>gt;\nThese correspond to <lt;code>gt;Animate<lt;/code>gt;, <lt;code>gt;Stay<lt;/code>gt; and <lt;code>gt;Move<lt;/code>gt; respectively, and work in the same way.<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nFor this example, let's make a <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt; action. Take the sit action of the shimeji you want and make a copy of it.<lt;br />gt;\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"Sit\" Type=\"Stay\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime11.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"0,0\" Duration=\"250\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nThen, modify it so it becomes a <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt; action instead of a <lt;code>gt;Stay<lt;/code>gt; as shown in the code snippet below.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nNote the new parameter, <lt;code>gt;Affordance<lt;/code>gt;. Any shimeji searching for an affordance will need to use this same value.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"SitAffordance\" Type=\"Embedded\" Class=\"com.group_finity.mascot.action.Broadcast\" Affordance=\"Cuddle\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime11.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"0,0\" Duration=\"250\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nCreate a new sequence for the action as normal.<lt;br />gt;\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"BroadcastAffordance\" Type=\"Sequence\"&gt;\n    &lt;ActionReference Name=\"SitAffordance\" /&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nAdd the new action into <lt;code>gt;behaviors.xml<lt;/code>gt; as appropriate. I recommend a high frequency as it relies on another shimeji noticing it.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nFor this example, place it in the \"On the Floor\" condition block.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Behavior Name=\"BroadcastAffordance\" Frequency=\"1200\" /&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\n<lt;h2>gt;ScanMove<lt;/h2>gt;\n<lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt; refers to moving towards a target shimeji that is <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;ing the affordance of interest.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nStart by making a copy of the run action in the shimeji that will be looking to <lt;code>gt;Interact<lt;/code>gt; with the first shimeji, as seen here.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"Run\" Type=\"Move\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime2.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime3.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nModify the action to the new <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt; type. Take note of the new attributes:\n<lt;ul>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;Affordance<lt;/code>gt;: The same name as you used before, in the <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt; action. These values must match!<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt;: When the shimeji reaches the <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;ing shimeji, this is the <lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt; (not <lt;code>gt;Action<lt;/code>gt;) to change to.<lt;/li>gt;\n\t<lt;li>gt;<lt;code>gt;TargetBehavior<lt;/code>gt;: The same, but for the <lt;code>gt;Broadcast<lt;/code>gt;ing shimeji, not the <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt;-ing one.<lt;/li>gt;\n<lt;/ul>gt;\nNote that the behaviour properties are expecting <lt;code>gt;Behavior<lt;/code>gt; names, which typically refer to sequences, not <lt;code>gt;Action<lt;/code>gt;s with image frames.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"RunAffordance\" Type=\"Embedded\" Class=\"com.group_finity.mascot.action.ScanMove\" Affordance=\"Cuddle\" Behavior=\"IHugYou\" TargetBehavior=\"IAmHugged\" BorderType=\"Floor\"&gt;\n    &lt;Animation&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime2.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime1.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Pose Image=\"/shime3.png\" ImageAnchor=\"64,128\" Velocity=\"-4,0\" Duration=\"2\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/Animation&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nCreate a new sequence for the action.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;\nNote the small Stand before the <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt;&mdash;this is important! Without it the <lt;code>gt;ScanMove<lt;/code>gt; will not work.\n<lt;pre>gt;\n&lt;Action Name=\"Hunt\" Type=\"Sequence\"&gt;\n    &lt;ActionReference Name=\"Stand\" Duration=\"${20+Math.random()*20}\" /&gt; &lt;!-- a small delay is needed to prevent an infinite loop --&gt;\n    &lt;ActionReference Name=\"RunAffordance\" /&gt;\n&lt;/Action&gt;\n<lt;/pre>gt;\nAdd into <lt;code>gt;behaviors.xml<lt;/code>gt; as normal. It should be a high frequency.\n<lt;br />gt;<lt;br />gt;","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
